parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, fuel gauge, and other essential gauges to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible for the driver to determine the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and other critical information, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Speedometer not working correctly
showing incorrect speeds
fuel gauge not working
tachometer not working
and other gauges malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
burning smell
electrical components melting
and fires starting in the dashboard or other areas of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or experience sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Vehicle losing power
stalling
sudden acceleration
and check engine light illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty brake and ABS systems can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake service light coming on
ABS light coming on
and brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty ignition switches and keys can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience and safety risks.
symptoms: Key getting stuck in the ignition
ignition switch not turning
and vehicle not starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rusted Brake Lines and Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system due to rusted brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
the brake warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of brake pressure
the vehicle is unable to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
the power steering pump makes a loud noise
the steering fluid is leaking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or sloppy
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
a clunking or knocking noise is heard from the steering column
the steering shaft is leaking fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sway bar can cause the loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is difficult to maneuver
the steering wheel feels loose or sloppy
a clunking or knocking noise is heard from the steering column
the sway bar is broken or damaged.
